Somehow related to TNC. The project documentaiton is a complete mess, with Attachment G coming from the listing. Every single Annual OPDR has been re-listed, some aren't completed and some that have been submitted have still not recieved credits. It's especially bewildering because doesn't seem like got a big upfront slug of credits. The same landowner (
Heartwood/Forestland Fund) used Finite Carbon to develop another project in the same region at a later date and that project DID get the slug of carbon (ACR248). I wonder if this was just a trial run that didn't pan out too well? Fairly confident that this project under-estimates credits due. My intuition is telling me that somehow this forestland group tried to do a project, got some initial credits, but the subsequent paperwork/verification stuff wasn't up to snuff. they approached TNC to take it off their hands -- which happens in 2019. by 2020, paperwork filed etc etc and backcredits issued.
